The Purdy School Cafeteria serves up a delicious, nutritious breakfast each morning, beginning at 8:45 AM each Monday and at 7:45 AM each Tuesday-Friday. KG-6 students are served in their classrooms; 7-12 students eat in the cafeteria! Join the Breakfast Club today!

Parents, Please Note: Class begins at 9:11 AM each Monday and at 8:15 AM each Tuesday-Friday. Breakfast service closes when class begins.

post_text: Work began today on our new gym floor, but not before a beloved PHS basketball alum took a final shot. Maintenance Director Glenn Terry played for the Eagles in their first game on our floor, in 1974. It was only fitting that he be given the honor of shooting one last hoop from the 46 year-old hardwood. We are so excited about our new floor, but today was bittersweet for Mr. Glenn and all Eagles that have left blood, sweat, tears and heart on the old floor.

post_text: BREAKING NEWS FROM THE NEST: PHS Baseball earns team and individual Academic All-State Honors! Our team earned the highest GPA in Class II, with a 3.71. Individual players receiving honors included: Clay Henderson, Jake Brown and Osiel Aldava. To earn Academic All-State accolades a player must meet a number of rigorous criteria, including maintaining a minimum GPA of 3.5 and being in the top 25% of his class. Congratulations to our Academic All-Staters and Coach Hughes!

post_text: ♥️♥️♥️ #PurdyEaglePride
shared_text:
Amy Hutson Harkey
March 24 at 11:33 AM ·

I had to run to get a few groceries today. As I was walking into the store, I saw one of our Purdy students checking out with a cart full of groceries. We were both so excited to see each other!

Asking what they were out doing- “Just buying something groceries for our pastor and his family. I’m going to run them to him now.” This simple statement and act of kindness brought tears to my eyes.

I cannot say how proud I am of our students. Looking out for others when it would be easier to look down and think only of ourselves and our families. This is true #purdyeaglepride.

shared_text:
Purdy Recycling Project
March 17 at 6:17 PM ·

For the first time in 15 years of operation, the Purdy Recycling Project is closed, along with the school, for at least a few weeks.

We need to change our name to Here to Help Purdy, as there really isn’t a Spanish Club anymore; we’ve been too busy.

We will miss seeing you all, but it will be nice to have a break too. Let’s all hope that the recycling markets improve while we’re away!

Please join the line and a volunteer will bring your meals to your vehicle in front of the High School Gym.

Purdy R-II Elementary
January 14 at 4:37 PM ·

Mrs. Bishop's Preschool Class got a special treat today, when 8th grader Austin Ash visited and read them a book. Fantastic job, Austin! #EagleExcellence #confidence
